You can iterate over the properties of this object, getting the pair `(key, item)`, using the following syntax:

    &lt;div ng-repeat=&quot;(key, item) in object.map&quot;&gt;
        &lt;button ng-click=&quot;load(key, item)&quot; type=&quot;button&quot;&gt;A&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;


In this way, you pass the `key` of the item to the `load` function. In this [link][1], you can find more details about this syntax for `ng-repeat`.



  [1]: https://docs.angularjs.org/api/ng/directive/ngRepeat#iterating-over-object-properties

